sentences: John H. Davison (31 May 1930 – 5 March 1999) was an American composer and pianist.

During 1964-1965, Davison was placed in the Kansas City (Missouri) Schools as part of the Music Educators National Conference's Contemporary Music Project, where he composed numerous works for band, chorus, and orchestra.
Davison taught at Haverford College from 1959 until his death.
1967 - Suite, 8 brass instruments (2 horns, 2 trumpets, 3 trombones, and tuba)
1968-69 - Sextet, English horn, violin, viola, violoncello, bass viola da gamba, and piano
1977 - Concertino for oboe and chamber orchestra
1980 - Sonata, euphonium (or trombone), tuba, and piano, Opus 73
1983 - Arthur's Return, bagpipes and string orchestra
1986 - Quintet, for trombone and string quartet
